    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Shortly after assuming the Vice Presidency of Student Affairs on December 1, 1964, Richard Cutler created the Office of Student-Community Relations, while eliminating the offices of the Dean of Women and Dean of Men.  The Office of Student-Community Relations was created to administer off-campus housing, student vehicle registration, and student-community concerns.</p>
      <p>Under the subsequent Vice Presidency of Robert Knauss, who was elected to that position in 1970, the functions of the Student-Community Relations Office were absorbed by the Housing Division, creating a single unified housing structure as recommended in 1965 by The President's Commission on Off-Campus Housing.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The records include regulations regarding student automobiles and resulting parking and traffic problems (1922-1968), planning and regulation of bicycles and motorcycles, housing inspection, and other matters of student concern.  The minutes of the University Council, composed of faculty members and students, containing emergency guidelines developed in 1970/1971 for dealing with campus unrest are included, as are a student credit union survey (1969), a health service study (1968-1969), and studies of university bookstores and campus recreation.</p>
    </scopecontent>
